264 1950 971 (    Suggest that the operator *\(\) for STL iterators be made) 971 SB
264 2000 420 (    into a const operation.) 420 SB
1689 1005 261 (    The function) 261 SB
1689 1055 697 (       void fn \(const ReverseIterator & x\) {) 697 SB
1689 1105 121 (        ...) 121 SB
1689 1155 240 (           y = x*;) 240 SB
1689 1205 121 (        ...) 121 SB
1689 1255 97 (       }) 97 SB
1689 1305 992 (     shows that the operation * is not defined as const in the) 992 SB
1689 1355 1143 (     reverse_iterator \(DRAFT 20 Sept 1994, 24.2.1.2\).  However, the) 1143 SB
1689 1405 991 (     body of the function does not modify the iterator object.) 991 SB
1689 1505 1157 (     Of course, const Iterator is different from const_iterator and from) 1157 SB
1689 1555 397 (     const const_iterator.) 397 SB
1689 1655 1132 (    This change was accepted in Monterey \(see N740\).  However, in) 1132 SB
1689 1705 1066 (    box 108, Corfield says it seems wrong to have const member) 1066 SB
1689 1755 1054 (    functions return a reference or a pointer to non-const T.  He) 1054 SB
1689 1805 1152 (    believes this should be reconsidered for operator* and operator->.) 1152 SB
1689 1905 1110 (    It has been further suggested in public review that const should) 1110 SB
1689 1955 1015 (    also be used the descriptions in 24.3.1.2.2 and 24.3.1.2.3.) 1015 SB
