264 1752 1187 (   Add addition and subtraction operators to forward, bidirectional and) 1187 SB
264 1802 314 (   reverse iterators.) 314 SB
264 1902 468 ( Alex Stepanov in lib-3611:) 468 SB
264 1952 1149 (   And if you reconsider the iterator requirements, you might as well) 1149 SB
264 2002 1193 (   reconsider the exclusion of + \(and related operators\) for non-random) 1193 SB
264 2052 930 (   iterator categories. I really hate advance and distance) 930 SB
1689 302 1166 (   templates. They are such a pain to use and they are really ugly. \(To) 1166 SB
1689 352 1218 (   see what I mean, take a look at what we now need to do to implement,) 1218 SB
1689 402 1167 (   say, lower_bound algorithm. It is in algo.h in our implementation.\)) 1167 SB
1689 502 1150 ( Later discussions show that this should not include output iterators,) 1150 SB
1689 552 821 ( and at most only - operations for input iterators.) 821 SB
1689 652 567 ( Discussion at Monterey meeting:) 567 SB
1689 702 1065 (    The library subgroup was in favor of this change.  It was felt) 1065 SB
1689 752 1036 (    that the added convenience of this is worthwhile.  The cost) 1036 SB
1689 802 1042 (    is in making it unclear that '+' can be a linear operation.  If) 1042 SB
1689 852 1122 (    operator+ is added to the base forward iterator in terms of using) 1122 SB
1689 902 984 (    the advance template it should add little cost to existing) 984 SB
1689 952 337 (    implementations.) 337 SB
1689 1052 368 ( Proposed Resolution:) 368 SB
1689 1102 897 (    See paper N0739R1 in the post-Monterey mailing.) 897 SB
