1689 352 786 ( Title:          Exceptions in ostreambuf_iterator) 786 SB
1689 402 757 ( Section:        24.4.4 [lib.ostreambuf.iterator]) 757 SB
1689 452 324 ( Status:         active) 324 SB
1689 502 219 ( Description:) 219 SB
1689 552 471 (         24.4.4.1 and 24.4.4.3:) 471 SB
1689 652 602 (Nathan Myers in message lib-3812:) 602 SB
1689 752 980 (As Plauger noted in some previous mail relating to locale,) 980 SB
1689 802 995 (the ostreambuf_iterator used to decouple iostream from the) 995 SB
1689 852 985 (locale facet interface provides no mechanism for reporting) 985 SB
1689 902 981 (output errors.  Changing the interface to allow the iterator) 981 SB
1689 952 1009 (to be compared against an "end" iterator doesn't help; again) 1009 SB
1689 1002 1032 (\(as Plauger points out\) the Output Iterator abstraction doesn't) 1032 SB
1689 1052 1040 (support comparison, and standard algorithms don't assume it.) 1040 SB
1689 1152 236 (** Discussion) 236 SB
1689 1252 1167 (Failures of abstraction in C++ are handled by throwing an exception.) 1167 SB
1689 1302 1071 (Output Iterators are, in general, allowed to throw if they cannot) 1071 SB
1689 1352 1058 (perform an operation; it is necessary only to specify that this is) 1058 SB
1689 1402 467 (what ostream_iterator does.) 467 SB
1689 1502 1151 (ostream and locale need to have specified what happens in the event) 1151 SB
1689 1552 1024 (of an output error, so the failure can be handled according to) 1024 SB
1689 1602 1108 (ostream's policy without imposing knowledge of it upon all locale) 1108 SB
1689 1652 107 (facets.) 107 SB
1689 1752 1129 (Another option is to note the error without throwing the exception.) 1129 SB
1689 1802 1184 (A member function can return a bool value to indicate if the operation) 1184 SB
1689 1852 106 (failed.) 106 SB
1689 1952 356 ( Proposed Resolution) 356 SB
1689 2052 1166 (1. Section 24.4.4.1 [lib.ostreambuf.iter.cons], for operator=\(charT c\),) 1166 SB
