264 1402 352 ( From public review:) 352 SB
264 1452 1157 (    Drawing iostream into an implementation that just needs iterators) 1157 SB
264 1502 381 (    is most unfortunate.) 381 SB
264 1602 1164 ( The current iterator header includes headers <ios> and <streambuf>) 1164 SB
264 1652 1056 ( to handle the stream iterators in 24.4.  This requires all of I/O) 1056 SB
264 1702 1089 ( to be included in the iterators header.  Yet I/O only needs this if) 1089 SB
264 1752 374 ( the iterators are used.) 374 SB
264 1852 1095 ( If a new header is used should it be in clause 24 or in clause 27?) 1095 SB
264 1902 775 ( Is <iositer> a good name for the new header?) 775 SB
264 2002 365 ( From Nathan Myers:) 365 SB
264 2052 438 ( Message c++std-lib-4174) 438 SB
1689 302 1024 ( There are natural places for each of these iterator templates.) 1024 SB
1689 352 694 (   Move istream_iterator<> to <istream>.) 694 SB
1689 402 710 (   Move ostream_iterator<> to <ostream>.) 710 SB
1689 452 1253 (   Move istreambuf_iterator<> and ostreambuf_iterator<> to <streambuf>.) 1253 SB
1689 502 865 (   Add forward declarations of all four to <iosfwd>.) 865 SB
1689 602 368 ( Proposed Resolution:) 368 SB
1689 652 845 (  Move the stream iterators into a separate header.) 845 SB
1689 752 1077 (  Update Table 55 \(pg 24-1\) to include header <iositer> in 24.4.) 1077 SB
1689 852 1060 (  Remove #include's for iosfwd, ios, and streambuf from 24.1.6) 1060 SB
1689 902 984 (  [lib.iterator.tags] Header <iterator> synopsis and tags for) 984 SB
1689 952 1124 (  subclause 24.4.  Create new header <iositer> in section 24.4 with) 1124 SB
1689 1002 1060 (  #include's for iterator, iosfwd, ios, and streambuf and tags for) 1060 SB
1689 1052 697 (  section 24.4 from the <iterator> header.) 697 SB
