264 752 1187 (BTW, this implementation is practically unusable for interactive input) 1187 SB
264 802 1044 (because of the read\(\) in the constructor \(which could be easily) 1044 SB
264 852 179 (eliminated) 179 SB
264 902 1155 (by introducing a bool member which tells whether or not the current) 1155 SB
264 952 133 (element) 133 SB
264 1002 255 (has been read\).) 255 SB
264 1102 438 (Nathan Myers in lib-4010) 438 SB
264 1152 1171 (I agree that the above change should be made.  Who will write up the) 1171 SB
264 1202 1130 (WP changes?  \(The delta in the WP would be quite small: I believe) 1130 SB
264 1252 1049 (it would involve two paragraphs.\)  This would not break code.) 1049 SB
264 1402 368 ( Proposed Resolution:) 368 SB
264 1452 1144 (    Changes to the semantics of input iterators accepted at the Tokyo) 1144 SB
264 1502 1087 (    meeting allow the read\(\) in the constructor to be delayed until) 1087 SB
264 1552 965 (    the iterator is referenced.  This leaves us the choice of:) 965 SB
264 1602 847 (       1\) Leave as a quality-of-implementation issue) 847 SB
264 1652 1188 (       2\) Add a bool member which identifies if the charT has been read) 1188 SB
264 1702 1083 (       3\) Mandate that istream iterators shall not perform the read) 1083 SB
264 1752 452 (          during construction.) 452 SB
264 1852 1011 (    Note that the description in para. 1 of 24.4.1 [lib.istream.) 1011 SB
264 1902 1095 (    iterator] must be changed to say that the iterator need not read) 1095 SB
264 1952 763 (    and store a value of T during construction.) 763 SB
264 2052 1142 (    A new bool member should not be needed now that input iterator) 1142 SB
1689 302 552 (    semantics have been changed.) 552 SB
