264 352 118 (24.4.3:) 118 SB
264 402 1125 (istreambuf_iterator should remove all references to proxy, whether) 1125 SB
264 452 1157 (or not Koenig's proposal passes to make more uniform the definition) 1157 SB
264 502 742 (of all input iterators. It is over specification.) 742 SB
264 602 150 (24.4.3.1:) 150 SB
264 652 1113 (istreambuf_iterator::proxy is not needed \(once istreambuf_iterator) 1113 SB
264 702 921 (is corrected as described below\). It should be removed.) 921 SB
264 802 150 (24.4.3.2:) 150 SB
264 852 949 (istreambuf_iterator\(basic_istream s\) should construct an) 949 SB
264 902 918 (end-of-stream iterator if s.rdbuf\(\) is null. Otherwise, it) 918 SB
264 952 1049 (should extract an element, as if by calling s->rdbuf\(\)->sgetc\(\),) 1049 SB
264 1002 975 (and save it for future delivery by operator*\(\). \(Lazy input,) 975 SB
264 1052 523 (however, should be permitted.\)) 523 SB
264 1152 150 (24.4.3.2:) 150 SB
264 1202 975 (istreambuf_iterator\(basic_streambuf *\) has no description) 975 SB
264 1302 150 (24.4.3.2:) 150 SB
264 1352 917 (istreambuf_iterator\(const proxy&\) should be removed.) 917 SB
264 1452 150 (24.4.3.3:) 150 SB
264 1502 929 (istreambuf_iterator::operator*\(\) should deliver a stored) 929 SB
264 1552 990 (element, or call sgetc\(\) on demand, then store the element.) 990 SB
264 1602 963 (It should *not* extract a character, since this violates the) 963 SB
264 1652 392 (input_iterator protocol.) 392 SB
264 1752 150 (24.4.3.4:) 150 SB
264 1802 989 (istreambuf_iterator::operator++\(\) Effects should say that it) 989 SB
264 1852 995 (alters the stored element as if by calling s->snextc\(\), where) 995 SB
264 1902 657 (s is the stored basic_streambuf pointer.) 657 SB
264 2002 150 (24.4.3.4:) 150 SB
264 2052 1035 (istreambuf_iterator::operator++\(int\) Effects should say that it) 1035 SB
1689 302 983 (saves a copy of *this, then calls operator++\(\), then returns) 983 SB
1689 352 1050 (the stored copy. Its return value should be istreambuf_iterator,) 1050 SB
1689 402 172 (not proxy.) 172 SB
1689 502 150 (24.4.3.8:) 150 SB
1689 552 1104 (template operator==\(istreambuf_iterator&, istreambuf_iterator&\)) 1104 SB
1689 602 475 (should have const operands.) 475 SB
1689 702 150 (24.4.3.8:) 150 SB
1689 752 1094 (template operator!=\(istreambuf_iterator&, istreambuf_iterator&\)) 1094 SB
1689 802 1088 (should have const operands. It also is ambiguous in the presence) 1088 SB
1689 852 1040 (of template<class T> operator!=\(T, T\) \(as are many operators) 1040 SB
1689 902 245 (in the library\).) 245 SB
1689 1002 118 (24.4.4:) 118 SB
1689 1052 943 (ostreambuf_iterator::equal is silly, since output iterators) 943 SB
1689 1102 864 (cannot in general be compared. It should be struck.) 864 SB
1689 1202 118 (24.4.4:) 118 SB
1689 1252 1191 (ostreambuf_iterator should remove all references to equal, operator==,) 1191 SB
1689 1302 900 (and operator!=. Output iterators cannot be compared.) 900 SB
1689 1402 118 (24.4.4:) 118 SB
1689 1452 1043 (ostreambuf_iterator should have a member ``bool fail\(\) const'') 1043 SB
1689 1502 876 (that returns true if any insertions into the controlled) 876 SB
1689 1552 1000 (basic_streambuf fail. This is desperately needed by ostream) 1000 SB
1689 1602 942 (to restore its original approved functionality when these) 942 SB
1689 1652 639 (iterators are used with facet num_put.) 639 SB
1689 1752 118 (24.4.4:) 118 SB
1689 1802 1086 (ostreambuf_iterator should add the member `bool failed\(\) const',) 1086 SB
1689 1852 1084 (which returns true only if an earlier insertion failed. It is needed) 1084 SB
1689 1902 1170 (by num_put in 22.2.2.2 to communicate insertion failures to inserters) 1170 SB
1689 1952 1186 (in 27.6.1.2. With this change, I believe the following example inserter) 1186 SB
