264 1702 1146 ( Iterator tags could be related by inheritance.  Doing so would allow) 1146 SB
264 1752 1110 ( a more generic solution to algorithms which are multiply defined) 1110 SB
264 1802 1084 ( based on iterator category.  For example, it might be possible to) 1084 SB
264 1852 1156 ( define to versions of an algorithm, one based on output_iterator and) 1156 SB
264 1902 1092 ( one based on forward_iterator.  Iterator categories which inherit) 1092 SB
264 1952 1037 ( from forward_iterator could use the second algorithm.  If the) 1037 SB
264 2002 985 ( categories are inherited, then the based classes should use) 985 SB
264 2052 212 ( inheritance.) 212 SB
