264 302 232 (-- Local Copy) 232 SB
264 352 899 ( This method requires the iterator to retain a separate) 899 SB
264 402 1107 ( copy of the object.  Any copy of the iterator has a distinct copy of) 1107 SB
264 452 184 ( the object.) 184 SB
264 552 1069 ( After a copy \(b\) is made of an iterator \(a\) then both a == b and) 1069 SB
264 602 364 ( *a == *b return true.) 364 SB
264 702 1066 ( If a copy is incremented, the value returned by dereferencing a) 1066 SB
264 752 782 ( previous copy is well-defined and unchanged.) 782 SB
264 852 1126 ( *a++ is valid and probably implemented by returning a temporary) 1126 SB
264 902 599 ( copy of the iterator for operator++.) 599 SB
264 1002 251 (-- Global Copy) 251 SB
264 1052 1059 ( This method allows the iterator to point to one particular copy) 1059 SB
264 1102 1034 ( of the object.  Any copy of the iterator may point to the same) 1034 SB
264 1152 317 ( copy of the object.) 317 SB
264 1252 1069 ( After a copy \(b\) is made of an iterator \(a\) then both a == b and) 1069 SB
264 1302 364 ( *a == *b return true.) 364 SB
264 1402 1106 ( If a copy is incremented, it is undefined behaviour to dereference) 1106 SB
264 1452 284 ( a previous copy.) 284 SB
264 1552 1126 ( *a++ is valid and probably implemented by returning a temporary) 1126 SB
264 1602 1100 ( instance of a proxy class \(although an iterator implemented with) 1100 SB
264 1652 1090 ( local copy semantics will conform to global copy requirements\).) 1090 SB
264 1752 261 (-- Unique Copy) 261 SB
264 1802 1004 ( This method allows only one valid copy of an iterator to be) 1004 SB
264 1852 395 ( dereferenced at a time.) 395 SB
264 1952 1041 ( After a copy \(b\) is made of an iterator \(a\) then a == b returns) 1041 SB
264 2002 953 ( true but *a == *b is undefined, because *a is undefined.) 953 SB
1689 302 1109 ( It is undefined behaviour to increment any iterator other than the) 1109 SB
1689 352 553 ( one which may be dereferenced.) 553 SB
1689 452 1092 ( *a++ is valid is probably implemented by returning a temporary) 1092 SB
1689 502 434 ( instance of a proxy class.) 434 SB
1689 602 368 ( Proposed Resolution:) 368 SB
1689 652 1114 (    Local copy is the status quo.  Global copy has been proposed by) 1114 SB
1689 702 1176 (    Andy Koenig, unique copy by Nathan Myers.  One specific method) 1176 SB
1689 752 1129 (    must be chosen.  Consensus seems to be towards global copy but) 1129 SB
1689 802 470 (    the issue is controversial.) 470 SB
1689 902 203 ( Resolution:) 203 SB
1689 952 1239 (    Resolved as in N0787/95-0187 with changes as proposed by motion 31) 1239 SB
1689 1002 374 (    as passed in Tokyo.) 374 SB
